Actual System Demand of Electricity represents actual electricity production.
Forecast System Demand of Electricity represents the predicted electricity production required to meet national consumption.
The Forecast Wind Generation represents a prediction of this total electrical output based on forecast weather data observed at regular 6 hour intervals.
The Actual Wind Generation represents an estimate of the total electrical output of all wind farms on the system.

System Generation represents the total electricity production on the system, including system losses, but net of generators' requirements. It includes an estimate of the power produced by wind generators, but excludes some non-centrally monitored generation (e.g. small scale CHP and microgeneration).

The East West Interconnector (EWIC) connects Ireland and Wales, between Deeside in North Wales and Woodland, Co. Meath in Ireland.

The Moyle Interconnector links the electricity grids of Northern Ireland and Scotland through submarine cables running between converter stations at Ballycronan More in Islandmagee, Co. Antrim and Auchencrosh in Ayrshire, Scotland. The link has a capacity of 500MW.
